Many UNA residents have recently received Vancouver Votes cards for the by-election to be held this month to elect 9 school trustees. This card may be confusing, in that it refers to residents of the University Endowment Lands and UEL voters, but not to UNA residents or voters. To clarify, UNA residents who are Canadian citizens and meet the other eligibility conditions may also vote in the election.

&nbsp;

Voting can be done either on <strong>October 10th</strong> (at Vancouver City Hall) or on Saturday, <strong>October 14th</strong>, from 8:00am to 8:00pm (at University Hill Secondary School). You will need to bring ID that proves you are a UNA resident. Please note that if you are not on the Voters List, you can register to vote at the voting place.

&nbsp;

There is also a by-election for one Vancouver City Councillor. UNA residents are not entitled to vote in that by-election and may only vote for school trustees.

&nbsp;

For further information, including eligibility for voting and the acceptable ID if you need to register at the voting place, see the <a href="http://vancouver.ca/files/cov/2017-by-election-uel-voter-information.pdf">Vancouver Votes card</a>.

[vc_row][vc_column][vc_column_text]<strong>Happy August, everyone!</strong>

&nbsp;

You might not think of UBC as the best place to spend your summer days. After all, it is a university campus! You imagine boring libraries, silent study halls, and zombies- I mean students, wandering around campus not knowing what to do with all their free time. But actually, UBC is more than just a school and it is way cooler than you think. It’s a major community, growing bigger every day, and that means there’s lots to do. What’s even better, everything is way less busy than in Metro Vancouver! That means summer fun without all the crowds and all the waiting. Here are my top 9 reasons why UBC is the best place to be this summer. Read on to discover your next summer adventure!

&nbsp;

<strong>9. Pacific Spirit Regional Park</strong>

Calling Pacific Spirit Park beautiful would be a grave understatement. Personally, I like to use the term “heaven” for this place. The park boasts 73 kilometres of walking and hiking trails, for people, dogs, bikes, and even horses! The trails are perfect for an easy and tranquil walk in the forest. I like to run in the park 2 or 3 times a week because of the fresh air, the peaceful environment, and the fact that I get to pass by SO MANY dogs! Seriously, the prospect of seeing the next cute pup keeps me going.

<strong><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-905" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/pacific-spirit-regional-park-1024x323.jpg" alt="pacific-spirit-regional-park" width="1024" height="323" /></strong>

&nbsp;

<strong>8. All the Dogs!</strong>

Yeah, I like dogs. Who doesn’t? But I think UBC is a hotspot for dog lovers, because there are pooches everywhere. With the high number of parks at UBC, it’s simply the perfect place to raise little ol’ Peaches. And that’s great for me, err, I mean everyone, because the people are nice and always let you play with their dogs. As a result, I have met some fascinating people and heard some great stories - simply by meeting their furry friends!

<strong><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-907" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/poochies-1024x427.jpg" alt="poochies" width="1024" height="427" /></strong>

&nbsp;

<strong>7. You'll Meet Great People</strong>

Speaking of the people, did I mention how great they are? Just in the past few weeks, I’ve met some fascinating individuals. I talked with a man for an hour who had just arrived in Vancouver that morning from Tanzania. He had spent the previous week climbing Mount Kilimanjaro (he made it to the top!). I also ran into a local Vancouver comedian who was outside helping his daughters catch Pokémon. How cute is that? The friendliness and openness of people in this community is a refreshing change from the typical business-as-usual feel of Metro Vancouver.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-658" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/blog-welcome-to-community.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 482px) 100vw, 482px" srcset="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/blog-welcome-to-community.jpg 900w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/blog-welcome-to-community-300x200.jpg 300w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/blog-welcome-to-community-768x512.jpg 768w" alt="blog-welcome-to-community" width="800" height="533" />

&nbsp;

<strong>6. Catching all those Pokémon</strong>

But it’s not just the people… it’s the Pokémon, too! There is an impressive amount of those weird little pocket monsters to catch at UBC. I've seen groups of people of all ages, wandering around with their phones, questing to be the best there ever was. So, playing Pokémon Go around UBC will not only help you catch them all, you’ll be going for a long and beautiful walk around campus!

&nbsp;

&nbsp;

<img class="alignnone wp-image-884" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/7.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 478px) 100vw, 478px" srcset="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/7.jpg 980w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/7-300x150.jpg 300w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/7-768x384.jpg 768w" alt="7" width="800" height="400" />

&nbsp;

<strong>5. The Amazing Views</strong>

Don’t look at your phone for too long, though, because you’ll miss the views of this beautiful place. The campus itself has gorgeous state-of-the-art architecture, scenic views of the islands and mountains beyond the inlet, and tons of green space. Want to have a picnic, toss the Frisbee around, or just soak up the sun on your favourite blanket? You can do it all here. Even better, our very own Wesbrook Community Centre is right next to Pacific Spirit Park, and the Old Barn Community Centre is just steps from UBC’s Botanical Gardens, several wonderful museums, and world-famous Wreck Beach. So no matter where you find yourself in this community, you will be surrounded by beauty.

&nbsp;

<strong><img class="alignnone size-large wp-image-915" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/Wild-1024x373.jpg" alt="Wild" width="1024" height="373" /></strong>

&nbsp;

<strong>4. Wreck Beach</strong>

Speaking of beauty, Wreck Beach’s attractiveness deserves its own entire article. North America’s largest clothing-optional beach is without-a-doubt the strangest, most beautiful spot in Vancouver. You can play nude bocce ball with beach locals, take a picturesque walk along the 7km shore, and tan those pasty buns – you’re blinding everyone!

<img class="alignnone wp-image-886" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/5.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 466px) 100vw, 466px" srcset="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/5.jpg 984w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/5-300x152.jpg 300w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/5-768x390.jpg 768w" alt="5" width="800" height="407" />

&nbsp;

<strong>3. The Splash Pad at Wesbrook Community Centre</strong>

And if you get a little too warm at Wreck Beach, you can cool off at Wesbrook Community Centre’s new Splash Pad. It’s a family and pet-friendly water park that is the perfect complement to your summer fun. Open every day this summer from 8 am to 8 pm, it’s designed to turn on only when you press the activation button. A happy summer is a water-saving summer.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-887" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/4.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 464px) 100vw, 464px" srcset="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/4.jpg 600w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/4-300x200.jpg 300w" alt="4" width="800" height="533" />

&nbsp;

<strong>2. We Are Community Programs</strong>

A happy summer is also one where you have fun and try new things. Wesbrook Community Centre and the Old Barn Community Centre offer hundreds of programs to help you stay active, healthy, and busy this summer. You can check out all we have to offer at <a href="http://www.wearecommunityvan.ca/">www.wearecommunityvan.ca</a>. This summer, I wanted to try something new so I’ve been attending our newest DDP Power Yoga class. Is it possible to feel simultaneously almost dead and more alive than ever? Who knew that getting my butt kicked twice a week would be my favourite summertime activity...

<img class="alignnone wp-image-829" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/yoga-hatha.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 438px) 100vw, 438px" srcset="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/yoga-hatha.jpg 900w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/yoga-hatha-300x267.jpg 300w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/07/yoga-hatha-768x683.jpg 768w" alt="yoga-hatha" width="800" height="711" />

&nbsp;

<strong>1. We Are Community Events</strong>

And finally, when you’re not busy with ballet, guitar lessons, or volleyball drop-ins this summer, take advantage of one of our awesome (and free!) community events. On Friday, August 12<sup>th</sup>, we’re hosting our second “Evening in the Park”, an outdoor live concert featuring Buckman Coe! And join us on Saturday, August 20<sup>th</sup> for the Old Barn Community Centre’s 10<sup>th</sup> birthday celebration. The Barn Raising will be a fantastic event with live music, a petting zoo, free BBQ, a pie eating contest, and so much more. Oh, and I’ll be there too, along with all of our amazing staff – what more could you want?

<img class="alignnone wp-image-888" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/DSC_1141.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 475px) 100vw, 475px" srcset="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/DSC_1141.jpg 640w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/DSC_1141-300x199.jpg 300w" alt="DSC_1141" width="800" height="531" />

&nbsp;

<strong>This Summer At UBC, You Will Never Be Bored!</strong>

With everything I’ve just mentioned, spending your summer days around UBC means you’re going to have a great time and you’ll never be bored. Just picture yourself, on a beautiful sunny day, at UBC: you start with a 9 am Hatha Yoga class at Wesbrook Community Centre, followed by a leisurely stroll through Pacific Spirit Park (where you meet delightful people and the cutest dogs ever). Next you make your way over to Wreck Beach, catching Pokemon along the way, and you have a beautiful ocean-side picnic. You feel relaxed, rejuvenated, and ready for more! The opportunities and activities are endless. That is why UBC really is the best place to be this summer.

<img class="alignnone wp-image-889" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/1.jpg" sizes="(max-width: 525px) 100vw, 525px" srcset="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/1.jpg 800w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/1-300x171.jpg 300w, http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/1-768x438.jpg 768w" alt="1" width="800" height="456" />

&nbsp;

<strong>What are your favourite things to do at UBC? Let me know in the comments below! </strong>

&nbsp;

Happy Summer Adventuring!

- Krysta[/vc_column_text][vc_column_text][/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]

&nbsp;

Dedicated to promoting creative expression and encouraging the success of local artists, we are throwing an exciting Craft &amp; Artistry Fair! This December, thousands of people will come together to celebrate the world of arts and crafts.

&nbsp;

It will be big.

&nbsp;

It will be merry.

&nbsp;

<em>But, there is still one thing missing from our Craft &amp; Artistry Fair…</em>

&nbsp;

<strong>You and your skillful talent!</strong>

&nbsp;

<img class="wp-image-938 alignleft" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/whome.jpg" alt="whome" width="252" height="335" />

<strong>Yeah, you!</strong>

You could be one of over 60 vendors at this exciting event! This is a wonderful opportunity for you to showcase your work, sell your goods, and connect with members of the community and beyond. Best of all, it's happening right around the holiday season! Your fantastical creations will be shared with family and friends, just the way they are meant to be.

The fair will be part of the larger <em>Wesbrook Village Family Fun Festival</em>, a big celebration attracting thousands of visitors. Other activities taking place include horse-drawn carriage rides, carolers, pictures with Santa, and more! You will have your own station along with other artists inside of Wesbrook Community Centre, a brand-new facility that offers hundreds of art, sport, and educational programs.

&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;">So, whether your craft is painting, ceramics, jewelry, sock puppets, <em>anything</em> - join us for this fabulous event!</p>
&nbsp;

Here's how to get started:
<ul>
 	<li>Apply here to be a vendor: <a href="http://tinyurl.com/WesbrookCraft">http://tinyurl.com/WesbrookCraft</a></li>
 	<li>Next: e-mail <strong>programs@myuna.ca</strong> with photos of 4-6 samples of your products.</li>
 	<li>Then we'll get in touch with you to set up a meeting. You'll show us the products you wish to sell and we'll go from there!</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;
<p style="text-align: center;"><strong>But hurry! The deadline to apply is Fri</strong><strong>day, August 26th, 2016</strong>.</p>
&nbsp;

<img class="size-full wp-image-944 aligncenter" src="http://wearecommunityvan.ca/wp-content/uploads/2016/08/HolidayCraftFair-2016-instagram-square.jpg" alt="HolidayCraftFair-2016-instagram-square" width="600" height="600" />

&nbsp;

Additional information:
<ul>
 	<li>Vendors will use tables measuring 8 feet by 30 inches.</li>
 	<li>Vendors will set up their own display using their own decorations and tablecloth.</li>
 	<li>The table, registration, and administrative fee is $75 with optional power access for an additional $15.</li>
 	<li>Please contact <strong>programs@myuna.ca</strong> or Taylor at <strong>tscott@myuna.ca</strong> if you have any questions!</li>
</ul>
&nbsp;

We look forward to meeting you and discovering your creations!

&nbsp;

- The Team at We Are Community

